  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 84736f00ca5690940aa2333ea4ce800b, type: 3}
  m_Name: SecondDream
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  dialogue:
  - When everything happened, my arm, Mom, when it all went. I don't think she ever
    stopped blaming herself for it.
  - She focused so hard on her work... top of her class, skipping grades like nothing...
    She grew up too fast. Especially when Dad left.
  - I should have tried harder to take the load off her back. She was carrying the
    weight of the world alone.
